com.tinkerpop.gremlin.process.graph.step.map.match

Interface Enumerator<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CrossJoinEnumerator, InnerJoinEnumerator, IteratorEnumerator, SerialEnumerator, SimpleEnumerator

    public interface Enumerator<T>
    An array of key/value maps accessible by index. The total size of the enumerator may be unknown when it is created; it grows when successive solutions are requested, computing as many as necessary.
    Author:
    Joshua Shinavier (http://fortytwo.net)

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • size

        int size()
        Returns:
        the number of solutions so far known; the enumerator has at least this many. This should be a relatively cheap operation.

      • visitSolution

        boolean visitSolution(int index,
                      BiConsumer<String,T> visitor)
        Provides access to a solution, allowing it to be printed, put into a map, etc.
        Parameters:
        index - the index of the solution
        visitor - a consumer for each key/value pair in the solution
        Returns:
        whether a solution exists at the given index and was visited
